# Captr Release Process

When the user asks to push live, follow ALL steps in order:

## 1. Build

```bash
cd /Users/simonamor/captr
xcodegen generate
xcodebuild -project Captr.xcodeproj -scheme Captr -configuration Release \
  -derivedDataPath ./build -clonedSourcePackagesDirPath ./build/SourcePackages \
  clean build
```

## 2. Re-sign Sparkle framework and app with Developer ID

```bash
APP="build/Build/Products/Release/Captr.app"
IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Simon Amor (D89WR7924X)"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP/Contents/Frameworks/Sparkle.framework/Versions/B/XPCServices/Downloader.xpc"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP/Contents/Frameworks/Sparkle.framework/Versions/B/XPCServices/Installer.xpc"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP/Contents/Frameworks/Sparkle.framework/Versions/B/Updater.app"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP/Contents/Frameworks/Sparkle.framework/Versions/B/Autoupdate"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP/Contents/Frameworks/Sparkle.framework"
codesign --force --timestamp --options runtime --sign "$IDENTITY" "$APP"
```

## 3. Create DMG

```bash
rm -f Captr.dmg /tmp/captr_temp.dmg
hdiutil create -volname "Captr" \
  -srcfolder "build/Build/Products/Release/Captr.app" \
  -ov -format UDZO /tmp/captr_temp.dmg
mv /tmp/captr_temp.dmg Captr.dmg
```

## 4. Notarize and staple

```bash
xcrun notarytool submit Captr.dmg --keychain-profile "notary" --wait
xcrun stapler staple Captr.dmg
```

## 5. Sign for Sparkle

```bash
./build/SourcePackages/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/sign_update Captr.dmg
```

Save the `sparkle:edSignature` and `length` from the output.

## 6. Update appcast.xml

- Add a new `<item>` at the top of the channel (keep old items for version history)
- Use the version from `Info.plist` (`CFBundleShortVersionString` and `CFBundleVersion`)
- Use the edSignature and length from step 5
- Set `pubDate` to current UTC date

## 7. Push to gh-pages

```bash
cp Captr.dmg /tmp/Captr_new.dmg
cp appcast.xml /tmp/appcast_new.xml
rm Captr.dmg
git checkout gh-pages
cp /tmp/Captr_new.dmg Captr.dmg
cp /tmp/appcast_new.xml appcast.xml
git add Captr.dmg appcast.xml
git commit -m "Release vX.Y"
git push origin gh-pages
git checkout main
rm -f /tmp/Captr_new.dmg /tmp/appcast_new.xml
```

## 8. Clear quarantine on local copy (optional)

```bash
xattr -cr build/Build/Products/Release/Captr.app
```

## Important

- Always bump `CFBundleShortVersionString` and `CFBundleVersion` in Info.plist before building if code has changed since last release
- The EdDSA signing key is stored in the macOS Keychain — do not regenerate it
- Notarization credentials are stored in Keychain under profile "notary" (Apple ID: dogcultstudio@gmail.com, Team: D89WR7924X)
